Eyeora Project Progress Notes Sential Vision System

Date: 15 September 2025
Prepared by: Akarshan Ghosh (Akku)

1Ô∏è‚É£ Backend Setup

Framework: FastAPI

Server running on local machine:

Detects LAN/Wi-Fi connection using psutil.

If LAN is connected ‚Üí shows Eyeora backend homepage with API docs link.

If no LAN ‚Üí redirects to Wi-Fi config page (SSID/password input).

IP Handling:

get_ip_addresses() prints all IPs (localhost + LAN/hotspot) for easy access.

Uvicorn runs on 0.0.0.0, making the backend accessible for devices on the same network.

Frontend-ready: Homepage is user-friendly and visually styled.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Network / Hotspot

Confirmed: Backend works over laptop hotspot.

Devices (ESP32-CAM, ESP32 Dev Board, phones) can send data as long as hotspot is active.

LAN vs Hotspot:

LAN connected ‚Üí backend runs normally.

LAN disconnected ‚Üí redirects to Wi-Fi config page.

IP addresses: Terminal prints all relevant access URLs for local & network access.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Backend Modular Update

Added upload endpoints for testing with frontend:

/upload_image ‚Üí stores images in uploads/images/.

/upload_video ‚Üí stores videos in uploads/videos/.

Folders are automatically created if they don‚Äôt exist.

File naming includes timestamp + original filename to avoid conflicts.

Endpoints ready to receive uploads from React frontend.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Frontend Plan & Structure

Purpose: Temporarily replace ESP32-CAM live feed with user-uploaded videos/images.

React app features:

Upload images/videos via POST API calls to backend.

Display success messages after upload.

Later: fetch YOLO detection results and display bounding boxes/overlays.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Backend & Frontend Integration Flow

User opens frontend ‚Üí selects image/video ‚Üí uploads to backend.

Backend saves file in proper folder (uploads/images/ or uploads/videos/).

Future: YOLO model processes the file and returns detections.

Frontend displays processed results (bounding boxes, detected objects, video frames with overlay).

6Ô∏è‚É£ YOLO Model (Next Phase)

Not implemented yet; currently we have placeholders for future integration.

Planned steps:

Add dummy YOLO endpoint ‚Üí returns sample detection data for frontend testing.

Replace dummy with real YOLO detection once model is integrated.

Support both images and videos.

